Created files:
- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/Codec/SystemTextJsonCodec.cs
    Implements IMessageCodec on top of System.Text.Json (8.0.0). The outer
    envelope is mapped to a private EnvelopeDto whose JsonPropertyName
    attributes pin the wire field names to camelCase (protocolVersion, kind,
    topic, correlationId, timestampUnixMs, payload). MessageKind is encoded as
    a lowercase string via JsonStringEnumConverter(JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase,
    allowIntegerValues: false), so unknown kind values surface as JsonException
    and are mapped to InvalidEnvelope. The codec keeps the payload as
    JsonElement so unknown payload structures pass through untouched.
    Encode pre-checks for null protocolVersion/topic and substitutes
    JsonValueKind.Undefined payloads with a static JSON null element to keep
    the serializer from throwing. Decode short-circuits on
    bytes.Length > MaxMessageSizeBytes (default 1 MiB) returning
    SizeLimitExceeded; catches JsonException to map to InvalidEnvelope; checks
    that protocolVersion is present, parses the leading major component, and
    returns ProtocolVersionMismatch when the major is not 1; finally validates
    that topic is non-empty before constructing the MessageEnvelope. Public
    constant SupportedProtocolVersion = "1.0" lets callers reference the
    expected version. Constructor accepts CoreIpcOptions and rejects null /
    non-positive MaxMessageSizeBytes.
