Implementation summary:
- Lives in namespace VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core.Codec inside the existing
  VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core asmdef. No new asmdef was needed because Core
  already references Abstractions and System.Text.Json.dll is auto-referenced
  through Runtime/Plugins/SystemTextJson/.
- Encoder uses JavaScriptEncoder.UnsafeRelaxedJsonEscaping so topic strings
  like "slot/1/assignment" are emitted with literal '/' to match the wire
  example in design.md §Data Models.
- Major-version parsing uses the leading dot-separated component; non-numeric
  protocolVersion strings fall through to InvalidEnvelope rather than
  ProtocolVersionMismatch, distinguishing "garbage" inputs from
  "syntactically-valid-but-incompatible" inputs.
- All exception paths inside Encode / Decode are caught and converted to
  IpcResult.Fail(...) so the codec never propagates exceptions to callers
  (Req 3.5 + the no-exceptions-across-API-boundary contract from design.md).

